2 main touches of balanced price are all you get at a #Bitcoin cycle bottom, and I don't think this time will be any different. It's simple.

In 2022, Bitcoin hit its first bottom on balanced price with a fall to 17.7k.
                                       
The second touch was clearly marked after the FTX drop at 16.5k.

Why did Bitcoin make a return to the lows in 2015 at 2? It was the bull market fake out and price had not risen much.

Why did Bitcoin come back to touch the line in 2020? A black swan that swept all the financial markets.

Bottom is in, and if you're anticipating and trying to predict the next "black swan", I don't think you're gonna make it, sorry.

But every cycle, #Bitcoin makes a fake cross over and fails to start the Bull Market.
                                                      
After the rise to 32k, the fake out is now completed.

There are two major support levels marked (red and blue) which have been retested as support after every fake out.

Bitcoin is now at the blue support line and red is not far away, downside is limited!

Time in the #Bitcoin N28CT green year is running out, and with it so is time at the best cycle buying prices.

Green year has called the bottom at 15.5k in November 2022, and predicted the best buying prices.
                           
It also came close to its next prediction, hitting the median price. This is half of the previous ATH. This year at $34,500.

Too many people are counting on another move to the lows, something that most people missed. 

Blue year is up next, the year when Bitcoin spends most of its time around the median price.

Accumulation time is dwindling, it's time to stop dreaming of another black swan.

Markets are both sad and amusing simultaneously. #Bitcoin is consistently trading around $26,000, struggling to reach $30,000‚Äîwhich isn't even half of its previous all-time high. Meanwhile, BlackRock and some of the largest asset managers worldwide are filing for a Bitcoin ETF because they want to get involved. And yet, people are hesitant to buy Bitcoin, even when they're advised repeatedly that it's for their own good.

However, as soon as Bitcoin hits new all-time highs and the price skyrockets to $100,000, $200,000, or maybe even $300,000, everyone, including their mothers, wants to buy Bitcoin.

It's unfortunate, but this is how market psychology often works...

These tops come every cycle in green accumulation year (after green vertical line) +/- 21 days from the date of the second halving, July 9th.
        
The first early top is typically the most aggressive, seeing pretty major decline in most cases. There will probably be some time to go before rally resumes.

The second early top will take place +/- 21 days from July 9th, 2024. 

Now is the time to be patient for price to pivot and enjoy the accumulation prices of green year!

$TET is really making a mark in the crypto world. They focus on privacy, security, and speed, and have set up a unique system for payments. 
The @tectumsocial team is more about showing what they can do rather than just talking about it.

A lot of people talk about how private @monero $XMR and @zcash $ZEC are, but not many know that $TET's SoftNote offers even better privacy for transactions.

Don't get caught up in the rumors and FUD. When you look closely, you'll see that $TET offers better security, can handle more users, keeps your details private, charges low fees, and is faster than many other cryptos, including Bitcoin.
Some cool things about $TET:

- It's super fast with 1.3 million transactions per second.
- It can help Bitcoin and other cryptos work faster.
- There will only ever be 10 million of them.
- They don't charge any fees.
- They've got a lot planned, including getting listed on more platforms.
Big shoutout to the @tectumsocial team for showing that with hard work and a good team, you can achieve great things in the crypto world.

Just like we were waiting for, the second move to the high loss buy zone is finally here for #Bitcoin on the RPV ratio!

The more I look, the more I am starting to see the possibility that downside may be tapped out.
         
The cycle bottom is confirmed with the first move to the lower portion of the buy zone. (green circle)

cleaned_data.original_text:
The middle of the #Bitcoin cycles all balance on what I would call a "baseline trend".

It's pretty common for price to have a huge unsustainable run up early in the cycle, where the first early top (yellow dots) takes place.
          
There's no way these aggressive climbs can be maintained, so price needs to find support that's a little more reasonable.

I know trendlines can be drawn many different ways, but it looks to me like the baseline is formed for the cycle. (check out the zoomed in view)

We've got our 1 drop below which happens on each baseline, and now the retest is in.

If this is true, Bitcoin doesn't go below it the rest of the cycle.

Even with the last drop in price, #Bitcoin 3-month volatility remains extremely low.

Volatility this low has never been seen outside of bullish price activity.

Then how did we just get the drop from 29k to 25k?
                       
This scenario is starting to look just like 2015, where Bitcoin made its first small move, and then returned to the lows.

And no... I'm not saying that Bitcoin is going back to the lows. I think in the end, this low volatility will be bullish, just like it's always been.

Most people seem to be expecting about one more drop for #Bitcoin, between the prices of 21k - 23.5k.

Is it possible? Sure! But it now seems the most surprising scenario would be an upwards continuation.
                                                        
It's not just that, you wouldn't believe the amount of people that are predicting another black swan for the cycle! Which... is an oxymoron by the way...

It seems there's a heavy case of recency bias. Sure, both of these things would be the case if this cycle played out exactly as the last, but a better question is, how could it be different?

I think there's a good chance that the bottom from the first early top (recent yellow circle) is in.

Next up, Second early top, +/- 21 days from July 9th, 2024. (next purple circle)

New ATHs: after Nov 28th, 2024. (next red circle)

Cycle Top: +/- 21 days from Nov 28th, 2025. 90-130k based on my personal expectations and models.

After 10 Months spent around the bottom purple and blue MVRV deviation bands, #Bitcoin has now made its second visit just below green.

This marked the local bottom in 2016 and would have in 2019... were it not for that pesky black swan of course.
            
The time we spent at the bottom this cycle was the same amount as 2015!

Ever think that just maybe... the downside from 2019 was so great because the run up was so massive? It even managed to reach the cycle top band.

The red band is currently priced at 54k. But don't worry, that goes up in the end game.

Which cycle do you think this resembles most?

gm

'heart bleeds love'
part 4 of the 'static' collection

some thoughts to accompany the art...

last november, on one of the bloodiest days in crypto history marked by the ftx collapse, 'heart bleeds love' was launched as a free 24-hour open edition. with minting capped at 1 per wallet, about 6,900 unique wallets participated in collecting the piece

since then, the landscape in this space has shifted a lot & while it has not been easy for most of us, from my perspective i feel like things are actually getting better. the art & relationships feel more authentic & the community has grown tighter. everyone knows each other

the friendships i made before the bear have deepened & the frens ive made during the hard times are based on solid foundations. it's as if the collective trauma we've all experienced over the past 2 years in this space have distilled the essence of our community, enhancing the depth & quality of everything. for that i am grateful & my heart bleeds love

üü• 2014 bear cycles took 59 weeks from cycle high to cycle low

üü• 2018 bear cycle took 52 weeks from cycle high to cycle low

üü• 2022 bear cycle took 54 weeks from cycle high to current cycle lows

Indicating the current low set of $15,600 on Nov 2022 was likely the low of this bear cycle

üü¢ Return to $BTC all time highs? = Dec 2024
üü¢ #bitcoin cycle top? = Oct 2025

Both the 2017 and 2021 #Bitcoin cycle tops could have been predicted in advance, to precision.

The measurement of the complete first cycle gains holds the key.

It is done by moving the first cycle's increase to the next Bitcoin support level.
        
This gives us two targets:

102k from the next highest resistance at green retrace point 3.

211k from the next highest support at blue retrace point 4.

So far the previous 2 cycles have always hit a local bottom support as a retrace, which would point to the higher target for the cycle.

But to be conservative, 103k is another point of interest.

These are the two most relevant price targets.

It will all depend on where price is when the day of reckoning comes according to my Halving Cycles Theory.

Next cycle top: +/- 21 days from Nov 28th, 2025. Projected on December 10th, 2025.

cleaned_data.original_text:
Are our #Bitcoin cycle top predictions too conservative this cycle?

With the average expectation at 150k, this observation says so.
                                            
Using a Fibonacci channel retrace, 164k would be the bare minimum by late 2025, with a more likely top being over 200k+!.

Cycles create fair value channels where Bitcoin spends most of its time. Using the channel top as a .236 retrace shows the exact same pattern replaying over and over.

Cycle tops exceed, and retest the fair value channel 100% retrace every time, no exceptions.

Only 2 things could invalidate this observation:

1. The fair value channel is not correct (unlikely given how many retests we have and the one move below)

2. An always accurate pattern fails.

My predictions are always much more conservative than this, but had to share since the pattern was there!

What do you think?

This is not far away, which means the real bull market is just around the corner!

The N28CT Price model gave you the #Bitcoin bottom at 15.5k in Nov 22, coming +/- 21 days from Nov 28th then.

It gave and continues to give you the best cycle buying prices during accumulation year.

It gave you a move to the median ($34,500 blue line) in green year.
     
Now looks much like previous green years, Bitcoin makes a move towards the median and then cools down. In many cases offering you a last chance buying opportunity.

Focus on the end game. This model calls for:

Cycle Top 140k 2025 +/- 21 days from Nov 28th.

27k bottom 2026 +/- 21 days from Nov 28th.

190k Top 2029 +/- 21 days from Nov 28th.

36k Bottom 2030 +/- 21 days from Nov 28th.

End of green year (Nov 28th, 2023) is typically a time of rally!

... don't blindly follow any one model, use data from many sources to come to conclusions, friendly tip from a profit veteran! (pinned tweet)

TRIGGER WARNING FOR BITCOIN MAXIMALISTS: 
Yes, I'm fully convinced about #Bitcoin. Within the first two days of researching Bitcoin in early 2017, I immediately grasped that Bitcoin might be the most significant phenomenon I'll ever witness on this planet. Over time, I began to ponder how Bitcoin could transform the world for the better. The world undoubtedly needs fair money now more than ever. However, I'm skeptical that Anarcho-capitalism will be beneficial, at least for the majority. To me, Anarcho-capitalism seems like a distilled form of Darwinism, potentially sidelining the vulnerable. Bitcoin maximalists who believe there will be enough capital allocated to assist society's weak might be overly optimistic. Humans aren't inherently benevolent. Just observe our surroundings and delve into history. The powerful often exploit the impoverished. I'd be elated to be proven wrong, but at 34, I doubt I'll live to see that day.

Did you know that when you buy #Bitcoin‚ÄØ‚ÄØ‚ÄØ on a centralized exchange, you are not actually buying Bitcoin? That's right. What you are actually buying is a claim to Bitcoin in the future. 

Some centralized exchanges don't even actually buy #Bitcoin‚ÄØ‚ÄØ‚ÄØwhen you make a purchase. They simply make an entry on their internal ledger, and that price becomes their future IOU to you. Knowing how degenerate and weak handed some of you are, some exchanges bet that: 

1) You'll never actually demand that they send you your #bitcoin‚ÄØ‚ÄØ‚ÄØ, so why bother buying it;
2) You'll panic sell on a dip, which many of these exchanges will help ignite, so why bother buying it?

You're just free money for them most of the time, and there is no bigger player of these games than Binance, the very firm manybof champion and cheer on. ü§°

You can, however,beat them at their own games by always removing your #Bitcoin‚ÄØ‚ÄØ‚ÄØ off exchange into self-custody. At this point, the exchange either has to buy the BTC to transfer to you or transfer what they bought for you originally. Either way, you force their hand to give up the goods. This gives them less BTC to play games with, too.

GET YOUR #BITCOIN‚ÄØ‚ÄØ‚ÄØ OFF EXCHANGES NOW!

The hash ribbons have produced one of the most accurate buy signals in #Bitcoin.

But most people seemed to forget about the most recent one in 2023 after the small drop in price.

Did you know this is only 1 of 2 occasions ever this signal has seen a negative return? The last occasion of this, 2012.
   
That's out of 14 signals total.

- 12 times this signal has been neutral or positive

- 7 times Bitcoin has seen large gains directly after a buy signal.

A signal has never falsely fired in a bear market downtrend.

Sure, we saw one drop after the buy signal appeared in August 2023, but no more than that has ever been seen.

Miners are rigs on!

Contrarian Opinion on the #Binance FUD:

My thoughts with Binance US is that it is a tiny ant in comparison to Binance International.  The #BNB  and Binance dying" FUD is absolute clout GARBAGE, and wishful thinking from idealistic #Bitcoin  Maxi's that don't understand much else in our industry.

Nearly every corporation at the top of an industry in the USA becomes ripe with corruptiomn and government/banking lobbyists.  That is a known fact.

I believe what we are seeing with people leaving Binance US is pressure from the US government/banks, in addition to the usual low volume from this bear market.  This is effectively pushing people out they do not control, so that they can install their own to control it.  This is similiar to what has happened at #Coinbase aka #IRSbase, where they were forced to essentially become IRS/government watchdogs for crypto investors now.

But most importantly, even if Binance US were to fail, apart from the fear porn crypto news headlines, it wouldn't even qualify as a black swan, by the numbers at least....Current CMC spot volume:

@binance  International - ~4.5 billion USD (#1)
@BinanceUS  - ~18 million (#66)

So by comparison of volume alone, Binance International is about 250X bigger than Binance US currently. 

So even in this scenario where Binance US fails, it is hardly a blip on the Binance radar elsewhere, and BNB/Binance will NOT be killed, contrary to the current sensalitonist narrative.

This is just my opinion - NFA

üí•üí•üí• Why You NEED To Own At Least 0.1 #Bitcoin | Michael Saylor 2024 Prediction:

‚ÄúI think there are only 3 things relevant right now and here are the 3 things.

The halving is coming with 100% certainty. 

And as far as I can see, most of the selling of #BTC in the market is the bitcoin miners that have to sell in order to pay their electricity bills & pay their debt expenses & their operating expenses.

So that amount of selling pressure is going to be cut in half in a few months, so we know that‚Äôs coming.

And then we know there a spot Bitcoin ETF coming and when that comes we plug into Wall Street and the entire banking system. 

And then finally that fair value accounting is coming and when that happens the objective will go away. 

And now you‚Äôre going to introduce this as a conversation into hundreds of boardrooms. 

They will not move in a week. They move quarterly but over the course of 12 quarters, you‚Äôll start to see company after company looking at this & you‚Äôll start to see a reallocation of assets.

At the end of the day, corporations only hold 2 assets. 

They hold cash and they hold bonds and so if Bitcoin is available as an asset pari passu to a bond, then you‚Äôll see a reallocation from bonds to Bitcoin. 

And then in the institutional investor side, you‚Äôve got all these people holding real estate, holding commodities, holding gold, holding ETF and S&P indexes and the like.

And if they start to reallocate and they will, 1% and 2% and 5%. Then you‚Äôre going to have something that has never happened in the history of the world which is you‚Äôve got an ETF on a commodity that is scarce.

Every other ETF in the world is on an asset that is not scarce, it‚Äôs inflationary. 

You can make more buildings, you can make more real estate, you can make more gold, you can make more commodities.

You can make $4 billion worth of any of any of those things. 

The underlying producers produce more of the asset to deflate or to depreciate the price. 

With Bitcoin, when $100 billion flows into the Bitcoin Spot ETF, there won‚Äôt be any ability for any producer to produce any more bitcoin.

And so you can‚Äôt really compare it to the spot and ETF of gold because gold is an inflationary asset and you can‚Äôt compare it to ETF‚Äôs on real estate or on bonds or on equity.

You really have to say this is the first time we ever plugged Wall Street into an asset that you cannot produce any more of.

And so nobody knows what will happen except that if you reason from first principles, you know that it‚Äôs got to actually perform better than all the other asset ETFs because the underlying fundamentals are just better.

But let me lay out three possible ways to invest in Bitcoin.

One if you buy Bitcoin, the underlying asset. 

The second is you buy the Spot ETF. 

The third is you buy @MicroStrategy.

Okay, so we talked about the headaches of buying Bitcoin, the underlying asset. 

You have to do it on a crypto exchange and put in place parallel custody, compliance, compensation control systems. So that‚Äôs the challenge of that.

The closest thing, the most compelling idea for a plain vanilla Bitcoin investment of an institutional investor is you buy the Spot ETF, you‚Äôre be getting 1 to 1 correlation.

For $1 million you put in you‚Äôre getting $1 million of Bitcoin. What‚Äôs the positive?

It‚Äôs marginal, it‚Äôs good collateral. I can buy in a second no money down and I don‚Äôt need to build parallel custody control compensation systems. 

So all my problems are handled by Wall Street.

What‚Äôs the cost? 50 to 100 basis points a year. 

Okay so if I charge you 1% per year over the course of 20 years or over the course of your lifetime, it means that kinda I take 20% of the money you invested at 1%. 

So there‚Äôs a cost 50 basis points means I get 10% of your money approximately.

But having said it all, I would pay you 50 to 100 basis point in order to be plugged in to Wall Street and it‚Äôs not a problem. 

It‚Äôs a lot better than the alternative which is rebuild all their systems and then finance themselves.

So MSTR is not that. MSTR you can think of as a levered long Bitcoin company that pays you a yield. 

Okay, so I‚Äôm not going to call it an ETF, because we are not a financial company but we have $4.4 billion plus of Bitcoin and $2 billion plus of debt. 

So what we‚Äôve done is we‚Äôve levered the balance sheet with debt that cost us about one and a half percent interest.

So MSTR takes advantage of its position as an operating company to do something that an ETF can‚Äôt do. 

An ETF can‚Äôt issue junk bonds. An ETF can‚Äôt issue convertible bonds. An ETF can‚Äôt do like an ATM, like we can could do, and an ETF can‚Äôt buy Bitcoin with cash flows.

So we have a lot of flexibility as an operating company and we don‚Äôt charge that fee. 

So we have $4.5 billion of bitcoin but we don‚Äôt charge $45 million a year.

So the real idea here is, what if I created an investment vehicle that paid you a yield instead of charging you a fee? 

And what If I was able to borrow money at one and a half percent interest?

I borrowed a billion dollars at 0% interest and bought Bitcoin with it. 

Let me give you a theoretical, if you get a 2% yield instead of paying a 1% fee, it‚Äôs 60% difference over the lifetime of your asset. 

So if you have a billion dollars invested and you‚Äôre getting a 2% yield, you‚Äôre actually picking up $20 million a year. Instead of paying $10 million a year.

So the dynamic of the company is very important. 

So you can imagine that if I don‚Äôt charge you a fee and if I have cheap leverage, the stock, the benefit accrues to the common stock shareholders. 

Because I went and I borrowed $2.2 billion at 1.5% interest and I bought Bitcoin with it.

So what‚Äôs the logical theoretical yield of Bitcoin? 

Is it more than 1.5% a year? 

Well let's say it was 15% a year. 

Then we‚Äôre scraping 14% positive real yield off of the debt. 

And so that would be 14% of a billion dollars or more, actually 14% of $2.2 billion. 

So that would be $300 million a year that accrues to the benefit of the common stock shareholders, you see.

This is the benefit of being an operating company. We can every quarter choose what to do. 

So some quarters we would issue junk bonds, other quarters we would issue convertible bonds, other quarters we would sell the equity, other quarters we would just use our own cash.

So the answer is there‚Äôs always going to be a good market and there‚Äôs always going to be a bad market. 

There‚Äôs things you shouldn‚Äôt do and there are things you should do.

So MSTR, to make a long story short, is a bit more complicated than a spot ETF, right? 

If you want something plain vanilla and simple, that it should basically correlate 1 to 1 with Bitcoin, after you pay the fee. 

Then you buy a Spot ETF. 

But if you wanted to actually try to outperform Bitcoin like MSTR‚Äôs outperformed Bitcoin. 

Our performance over the course of the three years is higher than bitcoin‚Äôs performance.

So if you want to outperform bitcoin or outperform the Spot ETF, you would do that by accretive financings.

This is where the understanding gap comes in.¬† People associate Bitcoin‚Äôs volatility with risk, but risk is ultimately a measure of uncertainty.¬† This strange new asset is widely viewed as terribly uncertain, and yet, its fundamental mechanics deterministically create the opposite result (when viewed on a 4+ year timeframe).

Bitcoin‚Äôs increasing scarcity is as certain as the laws of math and the forward march of time that its entire design is predicated on.¬† In my book, that puts Bitcoin‚Äôs degree of risk somewhere in the range of US Treasuries (if not considerably lower)."
